body:
@ax3l 

This thread is for discussion of ways we can get updates to Spack packages quickly.  Splitting the Spack repo (#1773) was proposed as one technical feature that might help with this goal.  But it's not immediately clear how much that approach would help with the stated goal, and I think we need more discussion on other ways to get updates quickly.  Hence this thread.

This is also a continuation of OT discussion on #1696
